title: Cameryn Harvey

title: CourseKata Data Analysis
text:
April 2024
Awarded Best Visualization from ASA DataFest at UCLA, for my group’s slide deck, findings, and presentation.

Analyzed 2,000,000+ rows across 6 datasets using R and Python for 48-hour competition of nearly 80 teams
Created and shared team findings in a 2-slide presentation to a panel of 25 judges and 400+ individuals
Developed strategic and compelling call-to-action suggestions to the CourseKata company representatives who provided the data
Achieved 97% prediction accuracy using random forest modeling

View my team’s winning slide deck here.

title: Predicting Obesity Status
text:
December 2024
Achieved 99.456% predicting accuracy with random forest modeling.

Cleaned 32,000+ observations of data and 29 predictors consisting of both numerical and categorical values
Narrowed down significant predictors and input values of ‘ntree’ and ‘mtry’ to reach most accurate predictions

The final written report can be seen here.

title: Cyber Psyche Website
text:
July 2024
Served as the head analyst and visualization specialist, using Tableau to craft each chart, plot, and graph post cleaning the data.

Developed and designed a website with WordPress to present findings from the analysis of 174,000+ rows of data across 2 datasets
These datasets contain various mental health metrics as well as geographical, socioeconomic, among other online player information

The website along with the different visualizations and findings can be viewed through this link.

title: Tennis Consulting
text:
May 2024 - Present
As part of UCLA’s Bruin Sports Analytics (BSA) Tennis Consulting Data Analytics and Tagging teams, I create, analyze, and visualize tennis data for the UCLA Women’s and Men’s Division 1 teams.

This data is self created by us through watching tennis matches and ‘tagging’ points in real time with our tagging software, and occasionally collected through SwingVision’s AI software
The match viewing website can be previewed here by signing in with the demo username and password provided on the site




Data Analytics
On the Data Analytics Team, I am a part of a small group that receives datasets provided by the Tagging Team and subsequently clean, visualize, and interpret the data. This process culminates to a written report that is sent directly to the UCLA tennis player whose match was analyzed with added suggestions and key insights to assist the player with future matches. An example of a finished report is available here.




Jupyter Notebook and EDA
We clean the data through a multitude of error checks within a Python Jupyter Notebook to generate CSV and JSON data formats. I generated a depth metric and exploratory data analysis (EDA) to the software’s error checks within this notebook, which can be viewed here.




Team Lead
As a tagging lead, I supervise a group of members through the technical aspects of the tagging software, teaching and encouraging them along the way. I help de-bug issues with the software while facilitating a productive and collaborative working environment. The tagging software can be found after signing in with the demo username and password provided on the site here.

title: Analysis of Tire Performance on Lap Speed
text:
March 2025
Determined that Hankook tires outperform Pirelli tires.
Sourced and cleaned data from Lamborghini Super Trofeo Series from the Laguna Seca track for the 2021-2024 seasons.

Analyzed the switch in tire companies from Pirelli to Hankook in the year 2023 and its impact on tire degradation and overall performance
Was the lead data analyst and created the visuals for data regarding Race 1, Race 2, and the different sectors within the course
Produced models for each sector lap times and the overall lap times with significant predictors and low variance inflation factors

The final written report can be can be seen here.
The GitHub Repository containing my code is observable here.
